ish/4005-49089/" data-ref-id="4005-49089">Trish</a>, and <a href="/vergil/4005-40613/" data-ref-id="4005-40613">Vergil</a> appear as playable characters)</li><li>X-Men: Children of the Atom (<a href="/akuma/4005-42685/" data-ref-id="4005-42685">Akuma</a> appears as a secret playable character)</li><li>X-Men versus Street Fighter</li></ul><h3>Other</h3><figure data-align="right" data-size="small" data-img-src="https://static1.comicvine.com/uploads/original/11/113509/5696088-jla%20x-men.png" data-ref-id="1300-5696088" data-ratio="0.71492403932082" data-width="1119" data-embed-type="image" style="width: 1119px"><a class="fluid-height" style="padding-bottom:71.5%" href="https://static1.comicvine.com/uploads/original/11/113509/5696088-jla%20x-men.png" data-ref-id="1300-5696088"><img alt="No Caption Provided" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" data-width="320" class="js-lazy-load-image" data-src="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/11/113509/5696088-jla%20x-men.jpg" data-srcset="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/11/113509/5696088-jla%20x-men.png 1119w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_super/11/113509/5696088-jla%20x-men.jpg 960w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11/113509/5696088-jla%20x-men.jpg 480w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/11/113509/5696088-jla%20x-men.jpg 320w"><noscript><img alt="No Caption Provided" src="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/11/113509/5696088-jla%20x-men.jpg" srcset="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/11/113509/5696088-jla%20x-men.png 1119w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_super/11/113509/5696088-jla%20x-men.jpg 960w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11/113509/5696088-jla%20x-men.jpg 480w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/11/113509/5696088-jla%20x-men.jpg 320w" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" data-width="320"></noscript></a></figure><ul><li>Fleer released a series of DC vs. Marvel trading cards, including Amalgam preview cards.</li><li>This was followed by a series of JLA vs. Avengers cards by Boris Vallejo, based on the team rosters of the 90''s.</li><li>This was subsequently followed by a series of X-Men vs. Teen Titans cards by Julie Bell, which like the JLA vs. Avengers series, formed a large image when placed together.</li></ul>', '{''api_detail_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/first_appeared_in_issue/4000-120645/'', ''id'': 120645, ''name'': "Walt Disney''s Thumper Meets the Seven Dwarfs", ''issue_number'': ''19''}', '55803', '{''icon_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/square_avatar/1/18154/9736193-1000001896.jpg'', ''medium_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/1/18154/9736193-1000001896.jpg'', ''screen_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/1/18154/9736193-1000001896.jpg'', ''screen_large_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_kubrick/1/18154/9736193-1000001896.jpg'', ''small_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/18154/9736193-1000001896.jpg'', ''super_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1/18154/9736193-1000001896.jpg'', ''thumb_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_avatar/1/18154/9736193-1000001896.jpg'', ''tiny_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/square_mini/1/18154/9736193-1000001896.jpg'', ''original_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1/18154/9736193-1000001896.jpg'', ''image_tags'': ''All Images,Comics,Covers''}', 'Crossover', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/crossover/4015-55803/', '1943');
INSERT INTO genres (aliases, api_detail_url, count_of_isssue_appearances, date_added, date_last_updated, deck, description, first_appeared_in_issue, id, image, name, site_detail_url, start_year) VALUES ('Promotional Giveaway
INSERT INTO genres (aliases, api_detail_url, count_of_isssue_appearances, date_added, date_last_updated, deck, description, first_appeared_in_issue, id, image, name, site_detail_url, start_year) VALUES (NULL, 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/concept/4015-55883/', '12199', '2010-05-10 12:55:08', '2026-02-18 06:29:33', 'Most frequent in publications where comics are not the focus or where there is a mix of comic and non-comic material, these are covers where the cover itself is not advertising the comic content but is either its own piece unrelated to any interior contents or is referencing a feature in the issue other than the comics.', '<p><em><strong>Note</strong>: Any cover tagged by this concept can only result in a creator credit for the production of the cover, no other pages can be credited on its behalf (characters, concepts, etc.). This concept should only be tagged for primary covers, variant covers inherently tend to be unrelated as the variant cover itself becomes the product and not the issue''s contents.</em></p>', '{''api_detail_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/first_appeared_in_issue/4000-717003/'', ''id'': 717003, ''name'': None, ''issue_number'': ''356''}', '55883', '{''icon_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/square_avatar/13/136525/5102297-1.jpg'', ''medium_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/13/136525/5102297-1.jpg'', ''screen_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/13/136525/5102297-1.jpg'', ''screen_large_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_kubrick/13/136525/5102297-1.jpg'', ''small_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/13/136525/5102297-1.jpg'', ''super_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/13/136525/5102297-1.jpg'', ''thumb_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_avatar/13/136525/5102297-1.jpg'', ''tiny_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/square_mini/13/136525/5102297-1.jpg'', ''original_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/13/136525/5102297-1.jpg'', ''image_tags'': ''All Images''}', 'Comics-Unrelated Cover', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/comics-unrelated-cover/4015-55883/', '1926');
INSERT INTO genres (aliases, api_detail_url, count_of_isssue_appearances, date_added, date_last_updated, deck, description, first_appeared_in_issue, id, image, name, site_detail_url, start_year) VALUES (NULL, 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/concept/4015-56004/', '30', '2011-04-17 07:53:24', '2012-01-20 13:42:15', 'Beware: It''s Assistant Editors'' Month! Don''t Say We Didn''t Warn You!', '<p>In 1984, <a data-ref-id="4010-31" href="/marvel/4010-31/" slug="marvel">Marvel Comics</a> had Assistant Editors'' Month under the premise that the editors were away at a convention and the assistant editors had free reign to do as they pleased. This resulted in some memorable, wacky or just plain terrible stories.     </p>', '{''api_detail_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/first_appeared_in_issue/4000-23881/'', ''id'': 23881, ''name'': None, ''issue_number'': ''159''}', '56004', '{''icon_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/square_avatar/3/38919/1775305-assistant_editors_month.jpg'', ''medium_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/3/38919/1775305-assistant_editors_month.jpg'', ''screen_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/3/38919/1775305-assistant_editors_month.jpg'', ''screen_large_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_kubrick/3/38919/1775305-assistant_editors_month.jpg'', ''small_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/3/38919/1775305-assistant_editors_month.jpg'', ''super_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/3/38919/1775305-assistant_editors_month.jpg'', ''thumb_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_avatar/3/38919/1775305-assistant_editors_month.jpg'', ''tiny_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/square_mini/3/38919/1775305-assistant_editors_month.jpg'', ''original_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/3/38919/1775305-assistant_editors_month.jpg'', ''image_tags'': ''All Images''}', 'Assistant Editors'' Month', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/assistant-editors-month/4015-56004/', '1984');
INSERT INTO genres (aliases, api_detail_url, count_of_isssue_appearances, date_added, date_last_updated, deck, description, first_appeared_in_issue, id, image, name, site_detail_url, start_year) VALUES (NULL, 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/concept/4015-56041/', '1452', '2011-07-23 10:14:30', '2025-04-14 05:34:16', 'A science fiction franchise comprised of multiple television series and movies, as well as novels, comic books, and other media within the expanded universe. Star Trek was originally created by Gene Roddenberry.', '<p><em><strong>Note</strong>: This page represents the Star Trek franchise as a whole, but with a special emphasis on its comic forms. It can be credited to any issue that is part of the Star Trek franchise but not issues that merely reference the franchise.</em></p><h2>Overview</h2><figure data-align="right" data-img-src="https://static.comicvine.com/uploads/original/5/58127/2543449-cage04.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-2543449" data-size="small" data-ratio="1.275" data-width="1000" data-embed-type="image" style="width: 1000px"><a class="fluid-height" style="padding-bottom:127.5%" href="https://static.comicvine.com/uploads/original/5/58127/2543449-cage04.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-2543449"><img alt="Gene Roddenberry (C), his future wife Majel Barrett (L) and Leonard Nimoy/Spock (R)" src="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/5/58127/2543449-cage04.jpg" srcset="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/5/58127/2543449-cage04.jpg 1000w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_super/5/58127/2543449-cage04.jpg 960w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/5/58127/2543449-cage04.jpg 752w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/5/58127/2543449-cage04.jpg 501w" sizes="(max-width: 501px) 100vw, 501px" data-width="501"></a><figcaption>Gene Roddenberry (C), his future wife Majel Barrett (L) and Leonard Nimoy/Spock (R)</figcaption></figure><p>The Star Trek franchise was created in 1964 by Gene Roddenberry, who eventually had his idea produced in 1966 in the form of the original television series <i>Star Trek</i>. Though relatively short-lived, lasting only three seasons before being cancelled in 1969, <i>Star Trek</i> proved incredibly popular. It spawned four live action spin-offs, one animated series and currently 11 (soon to be 12) feature films. It has became a cult phenomenon, and is currently one of the most popular science fiction franchises in the world.</p><p>It first appeared in comics in 1967 in Gold Key''s <a href="/star-trek/4050-2364/" data-ref-id="4050-2364">Star Trek</a>. Currently, <a href="/idw-publishing/4010-1190/" data-ref-id="4010-1190">IDW Publishing</a> holds the license to Star Trek Comics.</p><h2>Star Trek Universe Timeline</h2><h3>Enterprise (22nd Century: Captain Archer)</h3><figure data-align="right" data-img-src="https://static.comicvine.com/uploads/original/1/17981/2018970-star_trek_enterprise.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-2018970" data-size="small" data-ratio="0.762" data-width="500" data-embed-type="image" style="width: 500px"><a class="fluid-height" style="padding-bottom:76.2%" href="https://static.comicvine.com/uploads/original/1/17981/2018970-star_trek_enterprise.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-2018970"><img alt="Enterprise" src="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/17981/2018970-star_trek_enterprise.jpg" srcset="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1/17981/2018970-star_trek_enterprise.jpg 500w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/1/17981/2018970-star_trek_enterprise.jpg 480w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/17981/2018970-star_trek_enterprise.jpg 320w" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" data-width="320"></a><figcaption>Enterprise</figcaption></figure><p>In the early years of the starship program, before the formation of the Federation, there was a spaceship called the <a href="/uss-enterprise-nx-01/4055-60130/" data-ref-id="4055-60130">Enterprise</a>. Its crew members include Captain <a href="/jonathan-archer/4005-103645/" data-ref-id="4005-103645">Jonathan Archer</a>, science officer <a href="/t-pol/4005-103647/" data-ref-id="4005-103647">T''Pol</a>, chief engineer <a href="/trip-tucker/4005-168641/" data-ref-id="4005-168641">Trip Tucker</a>, tactical officer <a href="/malcolm-reed/4005-103649/" data-ref-id="4005-103649">Malcolm Reed</a>, communications officer <a href="/hoshi-sato/4005-168642/" data-ref-id="4005-168642">Hoshi Sato</a>, helmsman <a href="/travis-mayweather/4005-103650/" data-ref-id="4005-103650">Travis Mayweather</a>, and chief medical officer Dr <a href="/phlox/4005-103646/" data-ref-id="4005-103646">Phlox</a>.</p><h3>U.S.S. Enterprise (23rd Century: Captain Kirk)</h3><figure data-align="right" data-img-src="https://static.comicvine.com/uploads/original/1/17981/2021174-trek.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-2021174" data-size="small" data-ratio="0.75338753387534" data-width="369" data-embed-type="image" style="width: 369px"><a class="fluid-height" style="padding-bottom:75.3%" href="https://static.comicvine.com/uploads/original/1/17981/2021174-trek.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-2021174"><img alt="Original Series" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" data-width="320" class="js-lazy-load-image" data-src="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/17981/2021174-trek.jpg" data-srcset="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1/17981/2021174-trek.jpg 369w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/17981/2021174-trek.jpg 320w"><noscript><img alt="Original Series" src="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/17981/2021174-trek.jpg" srcset="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1/17981/2021174-trek.jpg 369w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/17981/2021174-trek.jpg 320w" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" data-width="320"></noscript></a><figcaption>Original Series</figcaption></figure><p>In the 23rd century, the <a href="/uss-enterprise/4055-54366/" data-ref-id="4055-54366">U.S.S. <i>Enterprise</i></a> begins its five-year mission to explore the outer reaches of space and make contact with alien civilizations. The crew includes Captain <a href="/james-t-kirk/4005-20078/" data-ref-id="4005-20078">James T. Kirk</a>, Science Officer <a href="/spock/4005-20079/" data-ref-id="4005-20079">Spock</a>, <a href="/leonard-mccoy/4005-20080/" data-ref-id="4005-20080">Dr. McCoy</a>, Lieutenant <a href="/nyota-uhura/4005-28180/" data-ref-id="4005-28180">Uhura</a>, chief engineer <a href="/montgomery-scott/4005-25747/" data-ref-id="4005-25747">Scotty</a>, and navigation experts and pilots <a href="/hikaru-sulu/4005-25746/" data-ref-id="4005-25746">Hikaru Sulu</a> and <a href="/pavel-chekov/4005-26347/" data-ref-id="4005-26347">Pavel Chekov</a>.</p><p>They faced many dangers including <a href="/harry-mudd/4005-28131/" data-ref-id="4005-28131">Harry Mudd</a>, the <a href="/klingons/4060-56525/" data-ref-id="4060-56525">Klingons</a>, the <a href="/romulans/4060-23900/" data-ref-id="4060-23900">Romulans</a> and most majorly: <a href="/khan-noonien-singh/4005-61065/" data-ref-id="4005-61065">Khan Noonien Singh</a>.</p><h3>Enterprise-D (24th Century: Captain Picard)</h3><figure data-align="right" data-img-src="https://static.comicvine.com/uploads/original/1/17981/2018971-tng_crew.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-2018971" data-size="small" data-ratio="0.652" data-width="500" data-embed-type="image" style="width: 500px"><a class="fluid-height" style="padding-bottom:65.2%" href="https://static.comicvine.com/uploads/original/1/17981/2018971-tng_crew.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-2018971"><img alt="Next Generation" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" data-width="320" class="js-lazy-load-image" data-src="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/17981/2018971-tng_crew.jpg" data-srcset="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1/17981/2018971-tng_crew.jpg 500w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/1/17981/2018971-tng_crew.jpg 480w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/17981/2018971-tng_crew.jpg 320w"><noscript><img alt="Next Generation" src="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/17981/2018971-tng_crew.jpg" srcset="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1/17981/2018971-tng_crew.jpg 500w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/1/17981/2018971-tng_crew.jpg 480w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/17981/2018971-tng_crew.jpg 320w" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" data-width="320"></noscript></a><figcaption>Next Generation</figcaption></figure><p>In the 24th century, an all-new crew of intergalactic travelers explore the farthest reaches of outer space aboard the <a href="/uss-enterprise-d/4055-56889/" data-ref-id="4055-56889"><i>Enterprise-</i>D</a>. The crew includes Captain <a href="/jean-luc-picard/4005-20105/" data-ref-id="4005-20105">Jean-Luc Picard</a>, Commander <a href="/william-riker/4005-20106/" data-ref-id="4005-20106">William Riker</a>, first officer <a href="/worf/4005-21619/" data-ref-id="4005-21619">Worf</a>, Counsellor <a href="/deanna-troi/4005-22691/" data-ref-id="4005-22691">Deanna Troi</a>, <a href="/dr-beverly-crusher/4005-11244/" data-ref-id="4005-11244">Dr Beverly Crusher</a>, chief engineer <a href="/geordi-la-forge/4005-20108/" data-ref-id="4005-20108">Geordi La Forge</a>, and second officer <a href="/data/4005-20109/" data-ref-id="4005-20109">Data</a>.</p><p>They face a new batch of foes including the <a href="/borg/4060-58374/" data-ref-id="4060-58374">Borg</a>, <a href="/q/4005-55490/" data-ref-id="4005-55490">Q</a> and so much more.</p><h3>Deep Space Nine (24th Century: Captain Sisko)</h3><figure data-align="right" data-img-src="https://static.comicvine.com/uploads/original/1/17981/2018968-ds9_crew.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-2018968" data-size="small" data-ratio="0.74955908289242" data-width="567" data-embed-type="image" style="width: 567px"><a class="fluid-height" style="padding-bottom:75.0%" href="https://static.comicvine.com/uploads/original/1/17981/2018968-ds9_crew.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-2018968"><img alt="Deep Space Nine" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" data-width="320" class="js-lazy-load-image" data-src="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/17981/2018968-ds9_crew.jpg" data-srcset="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1/17981/2018968-ds9_crew.jpg 567w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/1/17981/2018968-ds9_crew.jpg 480w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/17981/2018968-ds9_crew.jpg 320w"><noscript><img alt="Deep Space Nine" src="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/17981/2018968-ds9_crew.jpg" srcset="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1/17981/2018968-ds9_crew.jpg 567w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/1/17981/2018968-ds9_crew.jpg 480w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/17981/2018968-ds9_crew.jpg 320w" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" data-width="320"></noscript></a><figcaption>Deep Space Nine</figcaption></figure><p>Around the same time, the discovery of a stable wormhole that allows instant transportation between two distant quadrants of space prompts the creation of a station called "<a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/deep-space-nine-station/4055-56805/" data-ref-id="4055-56805">Deep Space Nine</a>". Crew members aboard this station include Commander (and later Captain) <a href="/benjamin-sisko/4005-25482/" data-ref-id="4005-25482">Benjamin Sisko</a>, first officer <a href="/kira-nerys/4005-14348/" data-ref-id="4005-14348">Kira Nerys</a>, chief of security <a href="/odo/4005-24139/" data-ref-id="4005-24139">Odo</a>, chief medical officer <a href="/julian-bashir/4005-20111/" data-ref-id="4005-20111">Julian Bashir</a>, science officer <a href="/jadzia-dax/4005-25428/" data-ref-id="4005-25428">Jadzia Dax</a>, counselor <a href="/ezri-dax/4005-20112/" data-ref-id="4005-20112">Ezri Dax</a>, strategic operations officer Worf, chief operations officer <a href="/miles-obrien/4005-55493/" data-ref-id="4005-55493">Miles O''Brien</a>, and <a href="/quark/4005-25632/" data-ref-id="4005-25632">Quark</a>.</p><h3>U.S.S. Voyager (24th Century: Captain Janeway)</h3><figure data-align="right" data-img-src="https://static.comicvine.com/uploads/original/1/17981/2018972-voyager_star_trek.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-2018972" data-size="small" data-ratio="0.63807531380753" data-width="478" data-embed-type="image" style="width: 478px"><a class="fluid-height" style="padding-bottom:63.8%" href="https://static.comicvine.com/uploads/original/1/17981/2018972-voyager_star_trek.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-2018972"><img alt="Voyager" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" data-width="320" class="js-lazy-load-image" data-src="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/17981/2018972-voyager_star_trek.jpg" data-srcset="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1/17981/2018972-voyager_star_trek.jpg 478w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/17981/2018972-voyager_star_trek.jpg 320w"><noscript><img alt="Voyager" src="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/17981/2018972-voyager_star_trek.jpg" srcset="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1/17981/2018972-voyager_star_trek.jpg 478w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/17981/2018972-voyager_star_trek.jpg 320w" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" data-width="320"></noscript></a><figcaption>Voyager</figcaption></figure><p>Meanwhile, the crew of the <a href="/uss-voyager/4055-56042/" data-ref-id="4055-56042">USS <i>Voyager</i></a> is stranded in the Delta Quadrant and forced to join with their <a href="/maquis/4060-56542/" data-ref-id="4060-56542">Maquis</a> enemies to make the seventy-year trek back to <a href="/united-federation-of-planets/4060-56645/" data-ref-id="4060-56645">Federation</a> space. Crew members include Captain <a href="/kathryn-janeway/4005-20071/" data-ref-id="4005-20071">Kathryn Janeway</a>, first officer <a href="/chakotay/4005-20072/" data-ref-id="4005-20072">Chakotay</a>, security officer <a href="/tuvok/4005-20076/" data-ref-id="4005-20076">Tuvok</a>, helmsman <a href="/tom-paris/4005-20074/" data-ref-id="4005-20074">Tom Paris</a>, chief engineer <a href="/belanna-torres/4005-20077/" data-ref-id="4005-20077">B''Elanna Torres</a>, operations officer <a href="/harry-kim/4005-20075/" data-ref-id="4005-20075">Harry Kim</a>, chief medical officer <a href="/the-doctor/4005-6023/" data-ref-id="4005-6023">The Doctor</a>, <a href="/neelix/4005-62317/" data-ref-id="4005-62317">Neelix</a>, nurse <a href="/kes/4005-62318/" data-ref-id="4005-62318">Kes</a>, and liberated Borg drone <a href="/seven-of-nine/4005-20073/" data-ref-id="4005-20073">Seven of Nine</a>.</p><h2>Alternate Realities</h2><h3>Mirror Universe</h3><p>The <a href="/mirror-universe/4015-55800/" data-ref-id="4015-55800">Mirror Universe</a> is a parallel universe where many people and places seemed to be the exact opposites of their normal selves in our universe. For example, good aspects who became evil, and evil became good.</p><h3>Last Generation</h3><p>A timeline which was not how it should be. General Worf of the Earth-ruling Klingons fights Jean-Luc Picard of the resistance. Meanwhile, an android known as Data thinks he can fix the time stream.</p><h3>New Film Series</h3><h4><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/star-trek/4025-108/" data-ref-id="4025-108">Star Trek</a> (2009)</h4><p>The young crew of the <i>Enterprise</i> is forced to deal with the arrival of a time-travelling Romulan, known as <a href="/nero/4005-61928/" data-ref-id="4005-61928">Nero</a>, hell-bent on seeking revenge against Spock. The Romulan''s actions alter the alternate reality''s time stream and the lives of the crew of Kirk and the crew of the Enterprise forever.</p><h4><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/star-trek-into-darkness/4025-1629/">Star Trek Into Darkness</a> (2013)</h4><p>Kirk and the rest of the crew have to deal with Kahn among other enemies.</p><h2>Prime Directive</h2><p>The Prime Directive is a non-interference policy of the United Federation of Planets. Under the Prime Directive, representatives of Federation member planets must not disturb the development of any civilization that has not yet independently developed warp drive technology. This means the Federation cannot make itself known to these civilizations at all, since any open interaction could result in a change to its history, culture or politics.</p><p>Under the Prime Directive, non-warp cultures can be studied in secret, using camoflagued research stations or infiltrating with the cultures in careful disguise. This research activity increases when a civilization nears its warp breakthrough, so that the Federation has a well-planned strategy for first contact after the initial warp experiment succeeds.</p><h4>Alternate Universe</h4><p>A particularly egregious violation of the Prime Directive is the subject of the mini-series <em>Star Trek: Countdown to Darkness</em>. In it, the Enterprise surveys the planet Phaedus and discovers that Robert April, former commander of the Enterprise, had intervened in a racial genocide on the planet. In violation of the Prime Directive, April had supplied arms to the minority Phaedans to ensure their survival.</p><p>Soon, Klingons begin to arm the majoriy Phaedans and the racial conflict on the planet turns into a proxy war between the Klingons and rouge elements within Starfleet. April is captured and detained by the Enterprise, but the damage to the Phaedan civilization is done. The irreversible nature of these changes underscores the importance of the Prime Directive as Federation policy.</p>', '{''api_detail_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/first_appeared_in_issue/4000-9475/'', ''id'': 9475, ''name'': ''The Planet Of No Return'', ''issue_number'': ''1''}', '56041', '{''icon_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/square_avatar/1/17981/1925254-42bb634940bdcb84756559124c06bc181280868218_full.png'', ''medium_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/1/17981/1925254-42bb634940bdcb84756559124c06bc181280868218_full.png'', ''screen_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/1/17981/1925254-42bb634940bdcb84756559124c06bc181280868218_full.png'', ''screen_large_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_kubrick/1/17981/1925254-42bb634940bdcb84756559124c06bc181280868218_full.png'', ''small_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/1/17981/1925254-42bb634940bdcb84756559124c06bc181280868218_full.png'', ''super_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/1/17981/1925254-42bb634940bdcb84756559124c06bc181280868218_full.png'', ''thumb_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_avatar/1/17981/1925254-42bb634940bdcb84756559124c06bc181280868218_full.png'', ''tiny_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/square_mini/1/17981/1925254-42bb634940bdcb84756559124c06bc181280868218_full.png'', ''original_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1/17981/1925254-42bb634940bdcb84756559124c06bc181280868218_full.png'', ''image_tags'': ''All Images,Star Trek General images''}', 'Star Trek', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/star-trek/4015-56041/', '1967');
INSERT INTO genres (aliases, api_detail_url, count_of_isssue_appearances, date_added, date_last_updated, deck, description, first_appeared_in_issue, id, image, name, site_detail_url, start_year) VALUES (NULL, 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/concept/4015-56081/', '222', '2011-12-11 08:12:51', '2025-04-23 17:45:50', 'The UK-based Eagle Awards were one of comic''s longest-established award ceremonies, launching in 1977 and continuing annually (with some interruptions and name changes) until 2014.', '<p><em><strong>Note</strong>: This page represents the comic industry award and can list all its winners and history in the description. However, it can only be credited to original printings of award-winning publications (including only the first issue in the case of serialized works), issues compiling multiple works that received the award or issues where winners are officially announced.</em></p><p>Fan nominated and voted awards for the comic industry''s creators and titles.</p>', '{''api_detail_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/first_appeared_in_issue/4000-16023/'', ''id'': 16023, ''name'': ''Howard the Barbarian'', ''issue_number'': ''1''}', '56081', '{''icon_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/square_avatar/3/38919/2120948-eagle_awards_logo.jpg'', ''medium_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/3/38919/2120948-eagle_awards_logo.jpg'', ''screen_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_medium/3/38919/2120948-eagle_awards_logo.jpg'', ''screen_large_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/screen_kubrick/3/38919/2120948-eagle_awards_logo.jpg'', ''small_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/3/38919/2120948-eagle_awards_logo.jpg'', ''super_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_large/3/38919/2120948-eagle_awards_logo.jpg'', ''thumb_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_avatar/3/38919/2120948-eagle_awards_logo.jpg'', ''tiny_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/square_mini/3/38919/2120948-eagle_awards_logo.jpg'', ''original_url'': ''https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/3/38919/2120948-eagle_awards_logo.jpg'', ''image_tags'': ''All Images''}', 'Eagle Awards', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/eagle-awards/4015-56081/', '1976');
